258
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:46,890
and see how this
switch gets turned.

259
00:13:46,890 --> 00:13:49,490
So we now have
this understanding

260
00:13:49,490 --> 00:13:54,680
of these individual protein
conformations, how they change,

261
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:57,230
and how they're
controlling energy

262
00:13:57,230 --> 00:14:00,080
allocation in photosynthesis.

263
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:03,380
And so with this fundamental
understanding of the protein

264
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:05,600
level properties,
we can now begin

265
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:09,320
to think about that gives us a
blueprint for what's happening

266
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,130
in organisms like this one.

267
00:14:11,130 --> 00:14:14,710
So we can think about
reallocating this,

268
00:14:14,710 --> 00:14:19,260
redistributing the energy
potentially to increase biomass,

269
00:14:19,260 --> 00:14:22,490
and maybe even one day
